{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 16:13:54.486375", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of what was submitted:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- localized faulty devices: host_1_2_3_1, host_2_3_3_1, host_2_4_2_3, host_2_4_4_1, and the access switches serving those host subnets\n- selected probable root cause(s): link_bandwidth_throttling, link_high_packet_corruption, receiver_resource_contention\n\nNotes:\n- These root causes were chosen to reflect the localized, intermittent latency/jitter observed on a small set of hosts and subnets. The report's limitations (many \"unknown\" test results and lack of device counters/logs) mean these are hypotheses rather than confirmed faults. Recommended next steps from the report (targeted pings/traceroutes, interface counters, and switch logs) should be executed to confirm and then remediate.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2600, "output_tokens": 187, "total_tokens": 2787, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
